I've just released version 1.1.0 of mgmt!

> 823 files changed, 25711 insertions(+), 5344 deletions(-)

This is a giant release that's much faster and has no known bugs or blockers. It
is incredibly polished, and I'm very proud of how far we've come. There are a
few breaking changes, but they "break safely" with compiler errors and are easy
to fix.

With that, here are a few highlights from the release:

* Function errors are reported with line/row and a visual marker of the error!

* A huge number of performance improvements were made, including to autoedge,
autogroup, graph swapping, deploys, and even function and resource engine perf.

* The scheduler was massively overhauled, and it can now do "withdraw" and more!

* Mgmt should always shut down in < 1000ms when you press ^C. If not it's a bug.

* We added a good number of benchmarks which we can run periodically.

* Deploy speed improved at least 500% by avoiding unnecessary round-trips.

* List, maps, etc do not use trailing commas anymore unless they are multiline.
Update your mcl. Mgmt shuts down safely if you forgot to remove one.

* Golang templates require title cased fields now. Update your templates. Mgmt
shuts down safely if you forgot one.

* You can now deploy over SSH in the same way that clients can read over SSH.

* The converger was rewritten to be not buggy and to support unconverged events!

* The engine has a new timeout metaparam which can set a precise deadline. Any
resource-specific timeout params should have been removed.

* We finally have the http:client resource! It supports long polling, and works
with http:server:file and friends. It's glorious. It can send/recv and it also
works with a net/http.response function. Resources play well with functions!

* The autoedge algorithm support resource hashable resource UID's for even
faster matching. A 10,000 node test went from 17,109ms to 53ms. Wow!

* The autogroup algorithm went from obscene numbers to quite low, eg: a 1,000
node set went from 162107ms -> 179ms. Wow!

And much more...


